
@startuml

' Define classes with attributes and associations

class Employee {
    - name: String
    - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class Planner extends Employee {
    - username: String
    - password: String
}

class AdministrativeStaff extends Employee {
    - fieldOfActivity: String
    - username: String
    - password: String
}

class Customer {
    - name: String
    - billingAddress: String
}

class Vehicle {
    - licensePlate: String
    - mileage: Integer
    + getType(): String
}

abstract class VehicleType {
    <<abstract>>
}

class RefrigeratedTruck extends VehicleType {}
class SmallVan extends VehicleType {}
class LoadingPlatform extends VehicleType {}
class BoxTruck extends VehicleType {}

Vehicle "1" -- "1" : has type -->
VehicleType "0..*" : <|-- "1"

class RepairShop {
    - name: String
    - address: String
}

class VehicleRepair {
    - employee: Employee
    - duration: Duration
    - cost: Double
    - repairShop: RepairShop
}

class Order {
    - comment: String
    - startTime: DateTime
    - endTime: DateTime
    - pickupAddress: String
    - deliveryAddress: String
}

class Driver extends Employee {
}

class PartnerCompany {
    - name: String
    - address: String
}

' Associations

Planner --> Order : assigns
Order --> Driver : assignedTo
Order --> Vehicle : uses
Order --> Customer : belongsTo
Order --> Planner : assignedBy
Order --> AdministrativeStaff : placedBy
Order --> PartnerCompany : placedWith (optional)

Vehicle --> VehicleRepair : may have
Employee --> VehicleRepair : performed by

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Employee**, **Planner**, and **AdministrativeStaff**: Inheritance structure for staff members.
- **Customer**, **Vehicle**, **VehicleType**, **PartnerCompany**: Entities representing business data.
- **VehicleType** is abstract to allow multiple types of vehicles.
- **Order** is central and connects customers, drivers, planners, vehicles, and partners.
- **VehicleRepair** links a vehicle to its repair details and the involved employee/shop.

